Definition.WordDefinition: Trajectory \Tra*ject"o*ry\, n.; pl. {Trajectories}. [Cf. F. trajectoire.] The curve which a body describes in space, as a planet or comet in its orbit, or stone thrown upward obliquely in the air. [1913 Webster]
trajectory n : the path followed by an object moving through space [syn: {flight}]
